 SECTION 1: ISSUE REPRODUCTION (6 Bugs Confirmed)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ BUG-1: Liquidation Long/Short Split Returns 0                      │
│ Severity: 🔴 CRITICAL  │  Tool: cg_liquidations                   │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ REPRODUCED: YES                                                    │
│ Input:  cg_liquidations(symbol="BTC", time_type="h24")             │
│ Result:                                                            │
│   total_liquidations_usd = 0  ← should be $86M+ (sum of exchanges)│
│   long_liquidations_usd  = 0  ← no breakdown available            │
│   short_liquidations_usd = 0  ← no breakdown available            │
│   long_percent  = 0                                                │
│   short_percent = 0                                                │
│   BUT per-exchange totals exist:                                   │
│     Hyperliquid: $19.3M                                            │
│     Bybit:       $15.3M                                            │
│     HTX:         $13.2M                                            │
│     Binance:     $11.3M                                            │
│     Bitget:      $10.9M                                            │
│     Gate:        $9.6M                                             │
│     OKX:         $4.3M                                             │
│     ... + 5 more exchanges                                         │
│                                                                    │
│ ROOT CAUSE: Upstream API returns total per-exchange but long/short │
│ split is 0 across all exchanges. Top-level aggregation inherits 0. │
│                                                                    │
│ IMPACT: Any strategy using long vs short liquidation balance for   │
│ sentiment analysis will always see "balanced" — completely useless.│
│ Small models will report "no liquidation pressure" when $86M was   │
│ actually liquidated.                                               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ BUG-2: Analysis Says "Shorts Dominate" With Zero Data              │
│ Severity: 🔴 CRITICAL  │  Tool: cg_liquidation_analysis           │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ REPRODUCED: YES                                                    │
│ Input:  cg_liquidation_analysis(symbol="BTC", time_type="h24")     │
│ Result:                                                            │
│   total_liquidations_usd = 0                                       │
│   long_liquidations_usd  = 0                                       │
│   short_liquidations_usd = 0                                       │
│   analysis.sentiment     = "Balanced liquidations"                 │
│   analysis.dominant_side = "shorts"  ← CONTRADICTION!              │
│   analysis.imbalance     = 0                                       │
│                                                                    │
│ ROOT CAUSE: Analysis layer has a default fallback to "shorts" when │
│ both sides are 0, rather than "unknown" or "data_unavailable".     │
│                                                                    │
│ IMPACT: Small model reads "shorts dominate" and may advise going   │
│ long based on phantom data. Directly misleading for trading.       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ BUG-3: Invalid Coin → "Check API KEY" Error                        │
│ Severity: 🟡 HIGH  │  Tool: cg_open_interest                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ REPRODUCED: YES                                                    │
│ Input:  cg_open_interest(symbol="INVALIDCOIN999")                  │
│ Result: "Failed to fetch open interest. Check COINGLASS_API_KEY."  │
│                                                                    │
│ ROOT CAUSE: Upstream returns HTTP 500 for invalid symbols. The     │
│ error handler catches all non-200 as "API KEY" issue.              │
│                                                                    │
│ IMPACT: Agent wastes time debugging auth instead of correcting     │
│ the symbol. User loses trust in the platform.                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ BUG-4: Tool Outputs Too Large for Small Models                     │
│ Severity: 🟡 HIGH  │  Affected: funding_rate, cg_liquidations     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ REPRODUCED: YES                                                    │
│ Input:  funding_rate(symbol="BTC")                                 │
│ Result: 5,847 chars of JSON (21 exchanges × uMargin + cMargin)    │
│                                                                    │
│ Analysis of output sizes:                                          │
│   funding_rate(BTC):      ~5.8K chars (manageable but bloated)     │
│   cg_liquidations(BTC):   ~2.5K chars (reasonable)                 │
│   cg_coins_market_data(): 25K-400K chars (KILLS small models)     │
│                                                                    │
│ ROOT CAUSE: Raw API data passed through without summarization.     │
│ No output budget enforcement.                                      │
│                                                                    │
│ IMPACT: 4K-context models (Gemini Flash Lite, GPT-3.5) cannot     │
│ process these responses. Even 8K models struggle with the full     │
│ coins_market_data dump.                                            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ BUG-5: Inconsistent Error Formats Across Tool Families             │
│ Severity: 🟡 MEDIUM  │  Affected: coinglass, coingecko, hl tools  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ REPRODUCED: YES                                                    │
│ Observed formats:                                                  │
│   Coinglass: "❌ Error: Failed to fetch X. Check API_KEY."        │
│   CoinGecko: HTTP status codes + raw JSON errors                   │
│   Hyperliquid: Various Python exception strings                    │
│                                                                    │
│ ROOT CAUSE: Each skill family implements its own error handling    │
│ with different conventions. No shared error schema.                 │
│                                                                    │
│ IMPACT: Agents need per-family error parsing logic. Small models   │
│ can't reliably distinguish "auth error" from "bad input" from      │
│ "network timeout" across different tools.                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ BUG-6: Funding Rate Format Inconsistency                           │
│ Severity: 🟢 LOW  │  Tool: funding_rate                           │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ REPRODUCED: YES                                                    │
│ Observed:                                                          │
│   Binance:     rate=0.000409, interval=8h                          │
│   Kraken:      rate=0.0001268, interval=1h                         │
│   Hyperliquid: rate=0.00125, interval=1h                           │
│   Bitfinex:    rate=0.00404, NO interval field                     │
│   HTX:         rate=-0.0120, NO interval field                     │
│                                                                    │
│ ROOT CAUSE: Exchanges report funding at different intervals.       │
│ Some include fundingIntervalHours, some don't. No normalization.   │
│                                                                    │
│ IMPACT: Comparing Binance (8h) vs Hyperliquid (1h) rates without │
│ normalization gives wrong conclusion. Kraken's 0.01% per 1h ≈     │
│ Binance's 0.04% per 8h, but raw numbers suggest Binance is 4x.   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

